%20of%20UK%20app%20users%20had%20their%20private%20information%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrities-with-hiv-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHIV%20statuses%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20shared%20with%20third%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20claim%2C%20lodged%20on%20Monday%20by%20UK-based%20law%20firm%20Austen%20Hays%2C%20accuses%20Grindr%20of%20breaching%20UK%20data-protection%20laws%20by%20sharing%20sensitive%20information%20with%20third%20parties%20without%20users'%20consent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20disclosed%20included%20users'%20HIV%20statuses%2C%20as%20well%20as%20data%20on%20their%20ethnicities%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeleted-dating-apps-stop-seeking-validation-happier-now-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esex%20lives%2C%20and%20sexual%20orientations%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20according%20to%20a%20press%20statement%20provided%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAusten%20Hays%20alleges%20that%20the%20data%20breaches%20occurred%20before%20April%202018%20and%20between%20May%202018%20and%20April%202020%2C%20%26quot%3Balthough%20they%20may%20extend%20to%20further%20periods%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%20data%20was%20shared%20with%20advertising%20companies%20Localytics%20and%20Apptimize%2C%20which%20the%20law%20firm%20said%20%26quot%3Bwould%20allow%20a%20potentially%20unlimited%20number%20of%20third%20parties%20to%20target%20and%2For%20customize%20advertisements%20to%20its%20users.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Austen%20Hayes%2C%20Grindr%20received%20payment%20from%20the%20third%20and%20fourth%20parties%20it%20shared%20personal%20data%20with%2C%20and%20it%20alleges%20that%20companies%20retained%20some%20of%20this%20data%20after%20the%20advertisements%20had%20been%20served.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20of%20us%20finding%20love%20and%20connections%20online%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20extremely%20personal%20data%20b