20obtained%20and%20lawfully%20used%20two%20visas%20within%20the%20previous%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two-year%20visa%20will%20normally%20be%20followed%20by%20a%20five-year%20visa%2C%20if%20the%20passport%20has%20sufficient%20validity%20remaining.%20During%20the%20validity%20period%20of%20these%20visas%2C%20holders%20enjoy%20travel%20rights%20equivalent%20to%20visa-free%20nationals%2C%20the%20EU%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20decision%20comes%20in%20the%20context%20of%20strengthened%20relations%20under%20the%20EU-India%20Common%20Agenda%20on%20Migration%20and%20Mobility%2C%20which%20seeks%20comprehensive%20cooperation%20on%20migration%20policy%20between%20the%20EU%20and%20India%2C%20with%20facilitation%20of%20people-to-people%20contacts%20being%20of%20key%20aspect%20due%20to%20the%20importance%20of%20India%20as%20a%20partner%20for%20the%20EU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESchengen%20visas%20allow%20the%20holder%20to%20travel%20freely%20in%20the%20Schengen%20area%20for%20short%20stays%20of%20a%20maximum%20of%2090%20days%20in%20any%20180-day%20period.%20The%20visas%20are%20not%20purpose-bound%2C%20but%20they%20do%20not%20grant%20the%20right%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Schengen%20area%20consists%20of%2029%20European%20countries%20(of%20which%2025%20are%20EU%20states)%3A%20Belgium%2C%20Bulgaria%2C%20Croatia%2C%20Czech%20Republic%2C%20Denmark%2C%20Germany%2C%20Estonia%2C%20Greece%2C%20Spain%2C%20France%2C%20Italy%2C%20Latvia%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20Luxembourg%2C%20Hungary%2C%20Malta%2C%20Netherlands%2C%20Austria%2C%20Poland%2C%20Portugal%2C%20Romania%2C%20Slovenia%2C%20Slovakia%2C%20Finland%20and%20Sweden%2C%20along%20with%20Iceland%2C%20Liechtenstein%2C%20Norway%2C%20and%20Switzerland.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713789300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Faog0qd2o_south-of-france-generic_625x300_22_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findians-can-apply-for-multiple-entry-sche